<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="716" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d716">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Pera,
                                        Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-02"><hi rend="italic">January 2,
                                1896</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Barnum distributes relief without restraint at Harpoot. Statement
                            published that I advised missionaries to leave is not true. Have not
                            given opinion, except privately to Mr. Dwight. Such publication weakens
                            my power to protect if they remain. No concert to enforce tranquillity
                            by the Powers; the Sultan knows this.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>